FR0.Description: A clean, foul-free surface; red and/or black AF paint or bare metal surface.

FR10.Description: Light shades of red and green (incipient slime). Bare metal and painted surfaces are visible beneath the fouling.

FR20.Description: Slime as dark green patches with yellow or brown coloured areas (advanced slime). Bare metal and painted surfaces may be obscured by the fouling.

FR30.Description: Grass filaments up to 3 inches (76 mm) in length, projections up to 1⁄4 inch (6.4 mm) in height; or flat network of filaments, green, yellow, or brown in color, or soft non calcareous fouling such as sea cucumbers, sea grapes, or sea squirts projecting up to 1⁄4 inch (6.4 mm) in height. The fouling cannot be easily wiped off by hand.

FR40.Description: Calcareous fouling in the form of tube worms less than 1⁄4 inch (6.4 mm) in diameter or height.

FR50.Description: Calcareous fouling in the form of barnacles, less than 1⁄4 inch (6.4 mm) in diameter or height.

FR60.Description: Combination of tubeworms and barnacles less than 1⁄4 inch (6.4mm) in diameter or height.

FR70.Description: Combination of tubeworms and barnacles greater than 1⁄4 inch (6.4 mm) in diameter or height.

FR80.Description: Tubeworms closely packed together and growing upright away from surface. Barnacles growing one on top of another, 1⁄4 inch (6.4 mm) or less in height. Calcareous shells appear clean or white in color.

FR90.Description: Dense growth of tubeworms with barnacles, 1⁄4 inch (6.4 mm) or greater in height. Calcareous shells brown in color (oysters and mussels); or with slime or grass overlay.

FR100.Description: All forms of fouling present, soft and hard, particularly soft sedentary animals without calcareous covering (tunicates) growing over various forms of hard growth.

PDR20.Description: AF paint missing from edges, corners, seams, welds rivet or bolt heads to expose anti corrosion (AC) paint. (undercoat)

PDR30.Description: AF paint missing from slightly curved or flat areas to expose underlying AC paint; An AF paint with visible brush swirl marks within the outermost layer – not extending into underlying layers of paint.

PDR40.Description: AF paint missing from intact blisters to expose AC paint or an AF coating with visible brush swirl marks exposing the next underlying layer of AF or AC paint.

PDR50.Description: AF blisters ruptured to expose intact AC paint.

PDR60.Description: AF/AC paint missing or peeling to expose steel substrate with corrosion present.

PDR70.Description: AF/AC paint removed from edges, corners, seams, welds rivet or bolt heads to expose steel substrate with corrosion present.

PDR80.Description: Ruptured AF/AC blisters on slightly curved or flat surfaces with corrosion or corrosion stains present.

PDR90.Description: Area corrosion of steel substrate with no AF/AC paint cover due to peeling or abrasion damage.

PDR100.Description: Area corrosion showing visible surface evidence of pitting, scaling, and roughening of steel substrate.

report.summary:
1. Niche Areas; Overall, the Niche areas of the vessel were observed to be less than 1% covered in soft
slime, consistent with FR-10. No calcareous growth was observed during the inspection.
2. Hull Plate; The hull plating was free from hard marine growth, consistent with FR-0.
3. AFC Condition; The AFC condition was found to be in overall good condition and relatively intact with
only minor blemishes observed, consistent with PDR-10-30
